definition.value: A branched amino octasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man group, while the beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end carries two alpha-L-Fuc residues via (1->3) and (1->6) linkages.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1,N(6)-etheno-2'-deoxyadenosine 5'-monophosphate residue; major species at pH 7.3.

An amino nonasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at positions 3 and 6 by beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man groups, while the D-GlcNAc carries two L-Fuc residues attached via alpha-(1->3)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 3,N(4)-etheno-2'-deoxycytidine 5'-monophosphate residue; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 1,N(2)-etheno-2'-deoxyguanosine 5'-monophosphate residue; major species at pH 7.3.
A sphingoid base(1+) that is the conjugate acid of N,N-dimethylsphingosine, obtained by protonation of the primary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An ethyl 3-(2-furyl)acrylate in which the double bond adopts a trans-configuration.
An organic cation that is 1-pyrroline bearing an N-(3-aminopropyl) substituent.
